bio.experienceSummary:
Hi everyone! Teaching and caring for children is both my passion and my purpose. Working as an Elementary School Teacher for the past 7 years, plus over 10 years of childcare experience has opened my eyes and heart to children's needs-- academically, socially, and emotionally. 

I absolutely love what I do and wish to broaden its impact through tutoring and childcare. I also hope to use my passion to help families establish normalcy during this uncertain time by providing individualized care and/or instruction. 

Some of my favorite tutoring subjects and activities include reading comprehension, writing, math, science, social studies, organization, study habits, and test-taking preparation.

In childcare positions, I love arts & crafts, exploring nature, games, imaginative play/theatre, building, developing communication skills, and working on whatever goals the parents have set for their child(ren). 

Hope to hear from you soon!
Corinne

description.originalText: Corrine joined our family in 2022 when our daughter was just 4 months old, and she has since become an integral part of our lives. Her nurturing and caring nature has made a profound impact on our family, and we are incredibly grateful for the time she has spent with us. From the beginning, Corrine demonstrated a deep commitment to our daughter’s well-being and development. She collaborated with us to create and implement monthly curriculum and provided thorough, insightful reports on our daughter's progress. Her support extended beyond childcare; she helped with housekeeping and took initiative to ease our workload. Her suggestions regarding meal planning, as well as her creative ideas for activities like arts and crafts, water play, and outings to the park, library, and neighborhood walks, were greatly appreciated. Her Montessori-inspired approach to fostering our daughter’s development and independence transformed our space into a mini classroom, offering a limitless learning experience. Corrine has provided exceptional care and support, and we highly recommend her to any family looking for someone dedicated and skilled.

bio.experienceSummary: I have extensive experience in the child care field, providing a loving, caring, and nurturing environment for children of all ages, from infants through early teens. Adaptable to special needs children and their care. I'm also a pet lover.

description.displayText: As a single parent, I couldn't have raised such a great son without her.   She was always there to support both my son and me.  She has great values and I trusted every decision she made when my son was in her care.  He is now 23 and both he and I still keep in touch with Cathi and see her regularly.  I would hire her in a heartbeat.....

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! I'm a former Montessori Preschool teacher, urban farmer, and non-profit professional with 5+ years of childcare experience. I've worked with kids ages 1-18 through daycares, nannying, summer camps, shelters, and group homes specifically for youth. I'm passionate about local food and farming, and hope to bring that into any classroom or home I am part of.

I am a mother of 2. I have had guardianship of 2 other children and fostered 3 brothers. My kids are 13 and 15 now but I've had custody of other children since I'm 22. I babysat (for free) all of my family and friends children so they can work since new Born and I have an 11 month old niece that I get for 1 week a month since she's 3 months old. I just have a deep love for children. Seeing and making children happy fills my heart and it my joy in life

I currently work as a Speech Language Pathology. I am looking for a summer position for babysitting. I have been babysitting for a number of years and have references upon request. Please reach out to me if you are looking for a sitter for your children. I have experience with newborns all the way through teens. I am comfortable with as many children as you have and also have experience with children with disabilities as well. I have a car and valid drivers license as well. Please feel free to reach out with any questions you may have. I look forward to hearing back!

Hello! My name is Ashley, I'm a nanny/babysitter with about 8 years professional experience, seeking a full time position. I am a very sweet, caring, trustworthy and reliable person. I have a passion for children and I truly enjoy being with them. I have experience with kids ranging from 5 months old to 12 years old. In my current and past jobs I had a variety of duties ranging from changing diapers, feeding, nap time, potty training, to grocery shopping, running errands or pick up/drop offs. I have a lot of fun with the kids I take care of. I enjoy bringing them to the park, going for strolls around the neighborhood or doing a bunch of other outdoor and indoor activities. I am capable of light cooking, cleaning or homework help and I am willing to help out all around. You can rely on me to always be there and treat your child/children as if they were one of my own. I hope to hear from you soon!

description.displayText: We were fortunate to find Ashley as a nanny on care.com for our 1.5 year old daughter. Sadly we moved to another state and couldn't take her with us! Ashley is kind, loving, energetic, playful, honest and reliable. Since day one Ashley was nothing short of amazing. She kept up with our high energy toddler and was her "go-go" girl (as our daughter liked to say. Our daughter was thriving and her vocabulary was expanding daily by being around Ashley. She is punctual, had never missed a day of work and was easy to communicate with. Our home was left tidy and our daughter was safe and always had a smile on her face when she was around Ashley. She has years of experience and multiple references.

bio.experienceSummary: As a parent of two grown children, Very dependable, reliable loving and honest. Available during the day/

I'm an enthusiastic childcare provider with a deep passion for nurturing the growth and development of young minds. My journey into the world of childcare was fueled by my desire to make a positive impact on children's lives and support families.

I have 24 years of hands-on experience caring for children of different age groups, from toddlers to preteens. I believe in creating a safe, nurturing, and stimulating environment where children can learn, play, and thrive. My patient and friendly nature allows me to connect easily with children and build strong relationships with them.

I prioritize open and effective communication with parents, ensuring they are regularly updated about their child's day and any matters that arise. I am also very comfortable enforcing household rules to provide a structured and consistent environment for the children in my care.

I'd describe my personality as fun, easy going and cheerful

I like working with kids because I love children. Love seeing their development growth and if I can have a piece of enhancing and empowering them to be great individuals then of course it's a pleasure. 

One thing you should know about me is your child is your precious jewel and my job is to keep that jewel save and treat it just as special as is.
I provide safety, care and fun to a child as I babysit. Ensuring they feel safe, comfortable to be themselves while having a wonderful time. Every child is different so I learn who they are, their personality, their likes and dislike. I am flexible and open to assisting in anyways I can. I love arts and craft, I'll play sport, I'll go on outings such as museum, park anywhere they want to go I'm willing to travel. Babysitting is not just a job but a passion.

description.originalText: Kiaora is a delightful and creative sitter who our five-year-old daughter immediately loved. We absolutely trust her to take great care of her.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello families! I am a very reliable, responsible, patient, and creative person who has approximately 4 years of experience caring for children, from infants to teenagers, I have been an au pair for 2 years, worked in day care for about a year and 5 months. With me, your children will receive appropriate care, and I'm willing to do additional other tasks if requested. Personally, I'm an organizer, planner, and multitasker, so minimum supervision is required. With all my skills and experience, I'm able to provide a supervised, safe, and stable environment for your little ones. I love children I know how important it is for them to have great people around them that care for them and I am capable to provide that.
